---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { COMPLIANCE } from '../site.config';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  name: 'Privacy Policy',
  url: 'https://learnmedicare.org/privacy',
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Learn Medicare"
  description="How Learn Medicare collects, uses, and protects the information you share with us."
  path="/privacy"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="subhead">Effective Date: July 14, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container legal">
      <p>
        Learn Medicare ("Learn Medicare," "we," "us," or "our") is an educational Medicare
        resource operated in connection with a licensed insurance agent, Kayla Price (NPN
        18530055). This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect through
        learnmedicare.org (the "Site"), how we use it, and the choices available to you. By
        using the Site, you agree to the practices described in this Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We collect information in the following ways:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Information you provide directly.</strong> When you fill out a form on the
          Site — such as requesting our free Medicare guide, enrolling in our email course,
          registering for the mini-course, or requesting a free plan review — we collect
          information such as your name, email address, phone number, ZIP code, and any other
          details you choose to provide.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Automatically collected information.</strong> Like most websites, we
          automatically collect certain technical information when you visit, including your IP
          address, browser type, device type, referring URL, pages viewed, and time spent on the
          Site. This is collected through cookies and similar tracking technologies, described
          further in Section 5 below.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Communications.</strong> If you contact us by phone, email, or chat, we retain
          a record of that communication, including any information you voluntarily provide.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Create and maintain a contact record for you in our customer relationship
          management system (GoHighLevel, "GHL"), so we can respond to your requests and follow
          up appropriately;</li>
        <li>Deliver the educational content you requested, including our free Medicare guide and
          mini-course lessons;</li>
        <li>Enroll you, with your consent, in an educational email drip sequence that delivers
          Medicare information over time via automated and manual email communications;</li>
        <li>Contact you by phone, text, or email about scheduling a complimentary, no-pressure
          plan review with a licensed agent, if you have requested one;</li>
        <li>Improve the Site's content, usability, and performance; and</li>
        <li>Comply with legal, regulatory, and recordkeeping obligations applicable to licensed
          insurance agents.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Consent to Contact (TCPA Disclosure)</h2>
      <p>
        By submitting a form on this Site and providing your telephone number and/or email
        address, you expressly consent to be contacted by Kayla Price and/or Price Services
        Group LLC by telephone (including by automatic telephone dialing systems and prerecorded
        or artificial voice messages), text message (SMS), and email regarding Medicare
        education and, where applicable, insurance products and services, even if your number is
        listed on a Do Not Call registry. Message and data rates may apply. Consent to be
        contacted is not a condition of purchasing any product or service. You may revoke your
        consent at any time by replying "STOP" to any text message, clicking "unsubscribe" in
        any email, or contacting us directly using the information in Section 8 below.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Email Drip / Educational Sequence</h2>
      <p>
        If you request our free guide, enroll in the mini-course, or otherwise opt in, you may
        be enrolled in an automated series of educational emails about Medicare. You may
        unsubscribe from this sequence at any time using the link provided in each email.
        Unsubscribing from marketing or educational emails does not automatically revoke consent
        to be contacted by phone or text unless you separately request that as described in
        Section 3.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
      <p>
        We use cookies, pixels, and similar technologies to operate the Site, remember your
        preferences (such as light/dark display mode), measure traffic and engagement, and
        support advertising and analytics tools. You can control cookies through your browser
        settings; disabling cookies may affect certain Site functionality. We do not knowingly
        sell personal information, as that term is defined under applicable state privacy laws.
      </p>

      <h2>6. How We Share Information</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information. We may share information with:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Service providers who help us operate the Site and manage contacts, including our
          CRM provider (GoHighLevel) and email/SMS delivery platforms, under confidentiality
          obligations;</li>
        <li>Carriers or business partners only where necessary to service a request you have
          affirmatively made, such as a plan review; and</li>
        <li>Government authorities or regulators, where required by law.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Data Retention and Security</h2>
      <p>
        We retain contact and form information for as long as reasonably necessary to fulfill
        the purposes described in this Policy and to comply with applicable insurance
        recordkeeping requirements. We use commercially reasonable administrative and technical
        safeguards to protect your information, but no method of transmission or storage is
        completely secure.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your Choices and Rights</h2>
      <p>
        You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of the personal information we
        hold about you, or ask us to stop contacting you, by emailing us at the address below.
        Depending on your state of residence, you may have additional rights under applicable
        privacy law.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Educational Content Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        This Site provides general educational information about Medicare and does not
        constitute medical, legal, financial, or insurance advice specific to your situation.
        {COMPLIANCE.tpmo} Kayla Price is a licensed insurance agent (NPN 18530055); nothing on
        this Site should be construed as a recommendation to enroll in, disenroll from, or
        change any specific plan.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This Site is not directed to individuals under the age of 18, and we do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Effective Date" above reflects
        the most recent revision. Continued use of the Site after changes are posted constitutes
        acceptance of the updated Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this Privacy Policy or your information may be directed to Kayla Price,
        licensed insurance agent (NPN 18530055), Price Services Group LLC, through the contact
        options listed on this Site.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-dark) 0%, #2b1147 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }
  .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .eyebrow { color: var(--color-teal); }
  .subhead { color: #e2d4f0; }
  .legal { max-width: 800px; }
  .legal h2 { margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 1.3rem; }
  .legal p, .legal li { color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; }
  .legal ul { padding-left: 1.4rem; }
</style>
